      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Basically restating my question from IRC (https://bitcoin-irc.chaincode.com/bitcoin-core-dev/2026-05-27#1779919187-1779922647;): Won't the slop horde open PR's for other issues? I'm not sure what evidence there is that avoiding the use of the label has reduced slop in general in the repo, but I don't have as much context as you and others do. But I'm pretty sure that all of the LLM's that opened issues and labeled them good first issue would have opened issues anyways just without the good first issue label, for example.\n\nIf it's feasible, maybe another solution is to disallow the use of the label by new contributors.",
